    </div>


    <div class="container">
        <br/>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4">
                <div class="thumbnail">
                    <img src="img/mobile-icon.png" alt="mobile-icon" height="150" width="200">
                    <div class="caption">
                        <h3 class="text-center">Mobile</h3>
                        <p>
                            A mobile device is a small computing device, typically small enough to be handheld
                            having a display screen with touch input and/or a miniature keyboard. Samsung, Sony,
                            HTC, LG, Motorola Mobility and Apple are just a few examples of the many manufacturers
                            that produce these types of devices. These typically include devices of varying
                            sizes such as tablet computers, e-readers, and smartphones.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-center">
                            <a href="/mobile" class="btn btn-primary" role="button">More on Mobile</a>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4">
                <div class="thumbnail">
                    <img src="img/bigdata-icon.png" alt="bigdata-icon" height="150" width="200">
                    <div class="caption">
                        <h3 class="text-center">Big Data</h3>
                        <p>
                            Big data is a broad term for data sets so large or complex that traditional data
                            processing applications are inadequate. Challenges include analysis, capture,
                            curation, search, sharing, storage, transfer, visualization, and information privacy.
                            The term often refers simply to the use of predictive analytics or other certain
                            advanced methods to extract value from data, and seldom to a particular size of data set.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-center">
                            <a href="/bigdata" class="btn btn-primary" role="button">More on Big Data</a>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4">
                <div class="thumbnail">
                    <img src="img/iot-icon.jpg" alt="iot-icon" height="150" width="235">
                    <div class="caption">
                        <h3 class="text-center">IoE &amp; IoT</h3>
                        <p>
                            Internet of Things (IoT) is the network of physical objects or "thing" embedded with
                            electronics, software, sensors and connectivity to enable it to achieve greater value
                            and service by exchanging data with the manufacturer, operator and/or other connected
                            devices. Where IoT just connects objects, but Internet of Everything (IoE) uses a
                            network to correlate people, process, data and things to become “intelligent”.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-center">
                            <a href="/iot" class="btn btn-primary" role="button">More on IoT &amp; IoE</a>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>



